included.description:
- Explored guerrilla design research methods to get "just enough insights" that informed strategic directions for start-up companies with very limited time and budget.
- Crafted compelling stories that clearly defined problems, evoked emotions, and generated enthusiasm among clients to take action.
- Advocated for human-centered design by involving clients in the process of user research and helping them taking ownership of the research findings.
included.title: User Experience Researcher and Strategist

included.description: While in graduate school, I worked as a graduate teaching associate and taught three courses in total. They were Design Fundamentals, Design Research and Design History.
included.title: Graduate Teaching Associate

included.description:
- Plan and conduct user experience research throughout the product development process, including ethnographies, participatory design sessions, competitive evaluations, concept testings, usability studies, etc.
- Foster collaboration among business stakeholders cross the enterprise to turn user research insights into actionable strategic directions.
- Move seamlessly between research and design. Create concept sketches, storyboards, wireframes, site maps and detailed design recommendations.
- Work in partnership with other researchers within Nationwide (market research and other UX researchers) to create comprehensive research strategies that merge quantitative data and qualitative stories.
- Developed expertise on insight translation -- planning ideation workshops, crafting compelling stories, visualizing complex data, etc.
included.title: User Experience Researcher and Strategist

included.description:
- Supported the entire design research process including creating homework, field research, data analysis, synthesis, data visualization and final presentation.
- Worked in collaboration with industrial designers to turn research into ideas and concepts by creating sketches, supporting brainstorming sessions and providing actionable design recommendations.
- Developed expertise on communicating research findings through information visualization.
included.title: Design Research Intern

included.summary:
As a experience researcher that lives at the intersection of user research, interaction design and strategy, I strive to create successful business and product solutions that lead to continuous business growth and seamless user experience. I achieve this by applying human-centered approach, playing the role of a dot-connector and often wearing multiple hats at the same time. 

My work spans all the way from front-end strategic research to tactical usability testing. I build deep empathy for people I work with to effectively communicate research findings, provide actionable recommendations and generate enthusiasm to turn research into next steps.

Specialties: qualitative user research, participatory design, design strategy,cross-channel experience, service design, usability, data analysis and synthesis, interaction design
included.headline: User Experience Researcher at Groupon

included.description: This research reveals the pattern among experienced practitioners, beginning practitioners and studentsâ processes of research planning and execution. A gap is identified between what current undergraduate education enables design students to do about design research and what design research practitioners are expected to achieve in industry. This research also has implications for the design research education and design research industry in terms of better preparing students to go into the design research industry and helping beginning practitioners make the transition to experienced practitioners
